configure: Fix incorrect argument type in gcry_md_open

The gcry_md_open function expects a gcry_md_hd_t * argument,
and not a gcry_md_hd_t argument (which is also a pointer behind
the typedef).  Future compilers will likely treat this as an
error, causing the check to fail unconditionally.
(main): Tidy up test code on various failures

Use correct rasqal_literal construction string ownership

(rasqal_query_convert_blank_node_to_anonymous_variable): Free the
literal string after the successful variable conversion.
(rasqal_new_triples_source): Clean up on fail in constructor
(main): cleanup up better on data URI failues

(rasqal_new_row_from_row_deep): Add to deep copy row

Does not deep copy the literals; just regular reference counting.
(main): Free data_dir_uri and data_dir_string in unit test code

Zero out uuid buffer before call

(rasqal_expression_evaluate_uuid): Zero out uuid buffer before call

(rasqal_query_results_rdf_write): Remove useless assigments

Remove setting predicate, object and row_node to NULL which will
never be used.  [Coverity CID 416504]
Promote number_to_move and i variables to yy_size_t
